From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rafly <rafly@zepharo>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] power: qcom: raise charge current limits for faster
 charging (topaz)

This patch is a TEMPLATE and REQUIRES confirmation of your actual
charger IC before it will do anything meaningful. Snapdragon 685
devices (topaz included) commonly use a Qualcomm SMB1355/SMB1390
(parallel charging) or QPNP-SMB5 family charger IC managed via the
qcom,qpnp-smb5 or qcom,smb1390 driver, configured through the board
.dts, not a single universal node name.

Hosted at: https://github.com/yougotme101/extra_patches
(0002-charging-speed-boost.patch)

If `git apply --check` fails in CI, the charger node name below
doesn't match your tree yet — update this file in the extra_patches
repo after running the grep commands below against your own source.

--- STEP 1: IDENTIFY YOUR REAL CHARGER NODE (run this first) ---

  grep -rn "qcom,smb\|qcom,qpnp-smb\|qcom,fastchg\|qcom,batt" \
    arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/*.dts arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/*.dtsi \
    2>/dev/null | head -30

  grep -rn "qcom,fcc-max-ua\|qcom,fastcharge-current-ma\|constant-charge-current-max-microamp" \
    arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/ 2>/dev/null

This will show the real property names and current node this tree
actually uses. The property names below are the common ones across
QCOM PMICs but MUST be checked against what step 1 found.

--- SAFETY NOTE ---

Raising charge current beyond what the battery cell and charger IC
were validated for by Xiaomi/the OEM increases heat and long-term
battery degradation risk, and in the worst case can be a fire/safety
hazard if pushed far past the cell's rated max charge current. This
patch raises the limit modestly (roughly +10-15% over stock) rather
than maximizing it. Verify your battery's actual rated max charge
current (usually in the battery's fuel-gauge/profile .dtsi or
datasheet silkscreen) before going further than this.

---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/topaz-charger-overlay.dtsi | 20 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/topaz-charger-overlay.dtsi

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/topaz-charger-overlay.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/topaz-charger-overlay.dtsi
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0000000
--- /dev/null
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/vendor/qcom/topaz-charger-overlay.dtsi
@@ -0,0 +1,20 @@
+/*
+ * Charging speed overlay for topaz (Redmi Note 12 4G, SM6225/685)
+ *
+ * Placeholder node name &pmic_charger below MUST be replaced with
+ * your tree's real charger node (commonly something like &smb5_charger,
+ * &qpnp_smb5, or &pmic_glink_power_supply depending on kernel/PMIC combo).
+ * Find it via the grep commands in this patch's commit message.
+ */
+
+&pmic_charger {
+	/* Stock values are typically ~3000000-4500000 (3.0-4.5A) depending
+	 * on region/charger bundled. These are modest +10-15% bumps —
+	 * adjust only after confirming stock values from your own tree. */
+	qcom,fcc-max-ua = <4600000>;       /* fast-charge current limit */
+	qcom,fastchg-current-ma = <4600>;  /* alternate property name, some trees use mA not uA */
+
+	/* Do NOT modify float/termination voltage (qcom,fv-max-uv or
+	 * constant-charge-voltage-max-microvolt) — that's set by the
+	 * battery cell chemistry limit, not a "speed" knob, and raising
+	 * it is a genuine safety risk (swelling/fire), unlike current. */
+};
